The paper deals with the problem of primary user localization in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
